CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 24, 1954, pg. 12 reads: "Easter Parade - The beautiful weather Sunday drew thousands of devout church-goers to their respective edifices to worship. And it also draw a glamorous parade of charming maids and matrons, bedecked in Easter finery.  Teenie Harris and Oceania Sockwell covered some fifteen churches to get the above photos...No. 7: Wesley Center focussed [sic] its attention of [sic] this group which included Jacqueline Richards, Jacqueline Scott, Gloria Walker and Earline Tibbs."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Jacqueline Richards, Jacqueline Scott, Gloria Walker, and Earline Tibbs, standing in front of Wesley Center A.M.E. Zion Church on Easter Sunday, Centre Avenue
